you mean " what the media tell you " .
i have more than a clue , i have excellent journalism to show me .
media is a plural word .
a medium is a means of transmitting information .
the town crier was a news medium , as were the troubadors of the middle ages .
theater and opera are media .
we have print media , spoken media such as radio , visual media such as tv and film .
we have electronic media such as this forum and the internet .
in each medium different persons , committees , and corporations exercise some editorial control , but in the us and much of the world , unitary control does n't exist and we have a broad diversity of views , and disagreement over the facts .
this is not true in russia where all media are strictly controlled by a state with absolute power , including the power to jail , kill or banish any opposition .

  these limits generally are based on assessments of health risk and calculations of concentrations that are associated with what the regulators believe to be negligibly small risks .

more futures contracts benefiting from a bond price increase versus those benefiting from a bond price decline ?
not that i care , but i question that math .
i believe every futures contract is a zero sum game where one speculator or hedger wins and the other loses the exact same amount ( and both pay commissions ) .
i do not believe there is such a thing as there being more contracts that benefit from one direction or the other in the futures market .
it is a zero sum game . (
unlike stocks which is a whole ' nother story ) .

 reference manual on scientific evidence : third edition 



  this sorta says it all 

  these limits generally are based on assessments of health risk and calculations of concentrations that are associated with what the regulators believe to be negligibly small risks .
the calculations are made after first identifying the total dose of a chemical that is safe ( poses a negligible risk ) and then determining the concentration of that chemical in the medium of concern that should not be exceeded if exposed individuals ( typically those at the high end of media contact ) are not to incur a dose greater than the safe one .

more futures contracts benefiting from a bond price increase versus those benefiting from a bond price decline ?
not that i care , but i question that math .
i believe every futures contract is a zero sum game where one speculator or hedger wins and the other loses the exact same amount ( and both pay commissions ) .
i do not believe there is such a thing as there being more contracts that benefit from one direction or the other in the futures market .
it is a zero sum game . (
unlike stocks which is a whole ' nother story ) .
perhaps this can be explained in a future column . (
no pun intended )

http://www.amren.com/news/2015/07/new-doj-statistics-on-race-and-violent-crime/ 

 this table can be used for a number of interesting calculations .
first , we find that during the 2012/2013 period , blacks committed an average of 560,600 violent crimes against whites , whereas whites committed only 99,403 such crimes against blacks .
this means blacks were the attackers in 84.9 percent of the violent crimes involving blacks and whites .
this figure is consistent with reports from 2008 , the last year doj released similar statistics .
perhaps not coincidentally , that was the year mr. obama was elected president .
interestingly , we find that violent interracial crime involving blacks and hispanics occurs in almost exactly the same proportions as black / white crime : blacks are the attackers 82.5 percent of the time , while hispanics are attackers only 17.5 percent of the time .

t would take an extraordinary set of circumstances for a flashbang to do that .
not impossible but very unlikely .
flashbangs do three things ... create a brilliant flash , a loud bang and a modest concussion wave .
those three things combined produce sensory overload which allow police time to enter a building and take people into custody .
they work best in enclosed spaces like bedrooms or living rooms .
out in the open , all three effects are greatly diminished .
she would almost certainly had to fall on top of it for something like to have a chance of happening .
also , flashbangs do n't create frag so that right there is a red flag .
look up " flashbang injuries " and you will see that they are almost always surface burns and bruising .
the injury she has is an explosive injury , not a diversionary device injury .

you mean " what the media tell you " .
i have more than a clue , i have excellent journalism to show me .
media is a plural word .
a medium is a means of transmitting information .
the town crier was a news medium , as were the troubadors of the middle ages .
theater and opera are media .
we have print media , spoken media such as radio , visual media such as tv and film .
we have electronic media such as this forum and the internet .
in each medium different persons , committees , and corporations exercise some editorial control , but in the us and much of the world , unitary control does n't exist and we have a broad diversity of views , and disagreement over the facts .
this is not true in russia where all media are strictly controlled by a state with absolute power , including the power to jail , kill or banish any opposition .

neither bill c-16 , the charter of rights and freedoms , nor any other law in canada forces you to recognize someone 's identity .
our laws only exist to prevent you from unlawfully discriminating against someone on the basis of their identity .
if you want to harbour ill - will towards people based on their race , ethnicity , nationality , age , gender or disability , there 's no law that says you ca n't .
but there are laws that prevent you from discriminating against people on those grounds , in certain situations .
like in the workplace .
it 's true that the charter 's rights and freedoms are only binding on the federal government per se .
nevertheless , the charter 's provisions oblige the federal government to pass laws which extend those rights and freedoms into certain areas .
the charter right to freedom from discrimination has little value if everyone but the federal government can violate it , whenever and wherever they like .

128522;&#128158;&#128584 ;
there are good reasons why no state awards their electors proportionally .
the whole number proportional system sharply increases the odds of no candidate getting the majority of electoral votes needed , leading to the selection of the president by the u.s. house of representatives , regardless of the popular vote anywhere .
it would not accurately reflect the nationwide popular vote ; 

 it would reduce the influence of any state , if not all states adopted .
it would not improve upon the current situation in which four out of five states and four out of five voters in the united states are ignored by presidential campaigns , but instead , would create a very small set of states in which only one electoral vote is in play ( while making most states politically irrelevant ) , 

 it would not make every vote equal .
it would not guarantee the presidency to the candidate with the most popular votes in the country .

how about this ?
http://www.amren.com/news/2015/07/new-doj-statistics-on-race-and-violent-crime/ 

 this table can be used for a number of interesting calculations .
first , we find that during the 2012/2013 period , blacks committed an average of 560,600 violent crimes against whites , whereas whites committed only 99,403 such crimes against blacks .
this means blacks were the attackers in 84.9 percent of the violent crimes involving blacks and whites .
this figure is consistent with reports from 2008 , the last year doj released similar statistics .
perhaps not coincidentally , that was the year mr. obama was elected president .
interestingly , we find that violent interracial crime involving blacks and hispanics occurs in almost exactly the same proportions as black / white crime : blacks are the attackers 82.5 percent of the time , while hispanics are attackers only 17.5 percent of the time .

les gara is so out of touch with basic business concepts and citing a geologist as your investment subject matter experts is just plain stupid .
pretty easy , business runs off of fixed and variable costs ; a subsidy offsets some of those costs .
without going into market mechanisms , if revenue exceeds cost businesses enter the market .
oil is a long term investment that has large fixed costs .
businesses are basing there investments based on that cost and an estimated tax structure .
when you change that tax structure it adds risk and creates instability which either reduces investment or increases operating .
the alaskan government choosing a dramatically changing tax structure in a extremely volatile market decreases investment and anyone with decent banking knowledge will tell you that .
so start thinking smarter alaska before it 's too late .

les gara is so out of touch with basic business concepts and citing a geologist as your investment subject matter experts is just plain stupid .
pretty easy , business runs off of fixed and variable costs ; a subsidy offsets some of those costs .
without going into market mechanisms , if revenue exceeds cost businesses enter the market .
oil is a long term investment that has large fixed costs .
businesses are basing there investments based on that cost and an estimated tax structure .
when you change that tax structure it adds risk and creates instability which either reduces investment or increases operating .

neither bill c-16 , the charter of rights and freedoms , nor any other law in canada forces you to recognize someone 's identity .
our laws only exist to prevent you from unlawfully discriminating against someone on the basis of their identity .
if you want to harbour ill - will towards people based on their race , ethnicity , nationality , age , gender or disability , there 's no law that says you ca n't .
but there are laws that prevent you from discriminating against people on those grounds , in certain situations .
like in the workplace .
it 's true that the charter 's rights and freedoms are only binding on the federal government per se .
nevertheless , the charter 's provisions oblige the federal government to pass laws which extend those rights and freedoms into certain areas .
the charter right to freedom from discrimination has little value if everyone but the federal government can violate it , whenever and wherever they like .

there are good reasons why no state awards their electors proportionally .
the whole number proportional system sharply increases the odds of no candidate getting the majority of electoral votes needed , leading to the selection of the president by the u.s. house of representatives , regardless of the popular vote anywhere .
it would not accurately reflect the nationwide popular vote ; 

 it would reduce the influence of any state , if not all states adopted .
it would not improve upon the current situation in which four out of five states and four out of five voters in the united states are ignored by presidential campaigns , but instead , would create a very small set of states in which only one electoral vote is in play ( while making most states politically irrelevant ) , 

 it would not make every vote equal .
it would not guarantee the presidency to the candidate with the most popular votes in the country .

 i am not claiming that wind and solar energy will meet all of our energy needs now or in the near future .
i 'm confident that fossil fuels will be used as long as i am around .

china reached peak coal in 2014 and is increasing the % of electrical power generated by renewables every year .

they largely have moved this way .
most their plans now throttle the bandwidth when the cap is exceeded instead of charging for overages ... so you can keep internet'ing away but at slower speeds and without surprise charges .
and their data caps are pretty generous ; i 'm paying for a 100 mbps connection with 250 gb cap per month -- no way do i ever approach 250 gb per month , even with a lot of netflix streaming .
unlimited bandwidth is a bad idea and that 's why those plans have largely gone away -- it invites abuse .
1 - 2 % of the users end up using 90 - 95 % of the bandwidth and slowing things down for everybody .

alaska is the perfect example of that by just looking at our glaciers .
that being said , the earth has cycles .
we have only been keeping accurate records for about 100 years .
the possibility of there being a cycle larger than 100 years is entirely possible .
we have no idea .
the real argument is whether or not global warming is man made and whether or not global warming is a naturally occurring cycle of the earth .
i for one believe the cycle of the earth is larger than we know and it is natures way of balancing things out .
throughout history , humans have a way of thinking the earth revolves around them .

they largely have moved this way .
most their plans now throttle the bandwidth when the cap is exceeded instead of charging for overages ... so you can keep internet'ing away but at slower speeds and without surprise charges .
and their data caps are pretty generous ; i 'm paying for a 100 mbps connection with 250 gb cap per month -- no way do i ever approach 250 gb per month , even with a lot of netflix streaming .
unlimited bandwidth is a bad idea and that 's why those plans have largely gone away -- it invites abuse .
1 - 2 % of the users end up using 90 - 95 % of the bandwidth and slowing things down for everybody .

i would very much like to comment on this topic but i seriously doubt that i can manage to do so in fewer than five pages .
this story takes me back to the summers i spent driving big rigs loaded with tomatoes .
one fine day the company radio was abuzz with a mini race war between the white and the hispanic truck drivers .
in fairness , we were working sixteen hour shifts with every eighth day off , so we were cranky .
finally , one hispanic driver said , " if we all left the us , you white people would starve because you 're too lazy to do the work required to feed yourselves . "
several white truckers clicked in and then clicked off without saying anything in response .
the truth of the statement was right in front of us in the fields we drove to and from .
we were exhausted from sitting in air - conditioned trucks while women and men of every age worked much , much harder for lower pay on the harvesters .
we deport the 11 million undocumented people at our peril .

richschlosser , 

 i am not claiming that wind and solar energy will meet all of our energy needs now or in the near future .
i 'm confident that fossil fuels will be used as long as i am around .
however , when it comes to the generation of electricity , renewables are now , in some locations , the cheapest and most environmentally attractive option .
clearly solar will not works as well in canada as in the atacama desert .
however , even in the oil and gas rich persian gulf solar is now the cheapest way to generate electricity and this was not the case before 2016 .
in the uae , saudi arabia and so on solar is being rolled out to power air conditioning water desalination and so on .
china reached peak coal in 2014 and is increasing the % of electrical power generated by renewables every year .
the world is changing , too quickly for some and too slowly for others .

t would take an extraordinary set of circumstances for a flashbang to do that .
not impossible but very unlikely .
flashbangs do three things ... create a brilliant flash , a loud bang and a modest concussion wave .
those three things combined produce sensory overload which allow police time to enter a building and take people into custody .
they work best in enclosed spaces like bedrooms or living rooms .
out in the open , all three effects are greatly diminished .
she would almost certainly had to fall on top of it for something like to have a chance of happening .
also , flashbangs do n't create frag so that right there is a red flag .
look up " flashbang injuries " and you will see that they are almost always surface burns and bruising .
the injury she has is an explosive injury , not a diversionary device injury .

another option , when conflict does occur , is to seek assistance from a mediator .
mediation is a voluntary process in which a neutral third party facilitates the negotiations of those involved in the conflict .
the parties craft their own solution to the problem that can go beyond what a court could ultimately decide and the process can bring finality , closure and certainty all at a fraction of the cost of drawn out court proceedings .
disputes among family members are particularly well suited to mediation given the range and intensity of issues usually involved .

i agree that this move was prompted by the government finally realizing that the cost of electricity has become a major political issue in ontario .
but i disagree with the tone of the editorial .
i think the fix should be in two stages ...   ( i ) immediate fee relief and ( ii ) a serious evaluation by an independent consultant on what needs to be done to fix the the hydro system .
in fairness to the government .
they inherited a problem including the various mistakes made in recent years but also the significant hydro debt that accumulated over the recent decades .
on the political side , i wish that both parties would outline their ideas on the future of hydro .
i criticize the liberals for presenting this fee relief as the longer - term solution and i criticize the conservatives for trying to appeal to the voters ' emotions by criticizing the liberals ' record but not offering their solution for fixing hydro .
they should be looking through the windshield , not the rear - view mirror .
one possible effect of the tax is the same as the immigration policy used in this example : it discourages people from coming to canada , investing their money in the country .

http://www.amren.com/news/2015/07/new-doj-statistics-on-race-and-violent-crime/ 
 new doj statistics on race and violent crime 

 this table can be used for a number of interesting calculations .
first , we find that during the 2012/2013 period , blacks committed an average of 560,600 violent crimes against whites , whereas whites committed only 99,403 such crimes against blacks .
this means blacks were the attackers in 84.9 percent of the violent crimes involving blacks and whites .
this figure is consistent with reports from 2008 , the last year doj released similar statistics .
perhaps not coincidentally , that was the year mr. obama was elected president .
interestingly , we find that violent interracial crime involving blacks and hispanics occurs in almost exactly the same proportions as black / white crime : blacks are the attackers 82.5 percent of the time , while hispanics are attackers only 17.5 percent of the time .

there is a difference between incentive and refusal .
funding essential government functions is not at issue .
profligate spending is the issue .
investing unlimited tax money ( bonds ) in downtown revitalization seems counterintuitive if the purpose is to decrease tax revenue ( bond payment ) elsewhere .
the ultimatum of snow plowing versus law enforcement indicates again that city government may operate in , shall we say , an altenate reality .
cui bono , you ask ?

http://www.amren.com/news/2015/07/new-doj-statistics-on-race-and-violent-crime/ 
 new doj statistics on race and violent crime 

 this table can be used for a number of interesting calculations .
first , we find that during the 2012/2013 period , blacks committed an average of 560,600 violent crimes against whites , whereas whites committed only 99,403 such crimes against blacks .
this means blacks were the attackers in 84.9 percent of the violent crimes involving blacks and whites .
this figure is consistent with reports from 2008 , the last year doj released similar statistics .
perhaps not coincidentally , that was the year mr. obama was elected president .
interestingly , we find that violent interracial crime involving blacks and hispanics occurs in almost exactly the same proportions as black / white crime : blacks are the attackers 82.5 percent of the time , while hispanics are attackers only 17.5 percent of the time .

another option , when conflict does occur , is to seek assistance from a mediator .
mediation is a voluntary process in which a neutral third party facilitates the negotiations of those involved in the conflict .
the parties craft their own solution to the problem that can go beyond what a court could ultimately decide and the process can bring finality , closure and certainty all at a fraction of the cost of drawn out court proceedings .
disputes among family members are particularly well suited to mediation given the range and intensity of issues usually involved .
